  "recommendation": "Annual-cycle revalidation is sufficient.",
  "justification": "The model's ongoing monitoring metrics do not indicate a need for immediate intervention. The Population Stability Index (PSI) of 0.06 is well below the standard industry action threshold of 0.1, signifying that the borrower population has not significantly shifted. This stability, coupled with the model's historically strong predictive accuracy (AUC = 0.84), suggests that the model continues to be relevant and performant. Triggering an out-of-cycle revalidation is not warranted by the data. The scheduled annual revalidation in 5 months remains the appropriate course of action."
